Epilepsy is a neurological condition which affects the nervous system, usually diagnosed after
a person has had at least two seizures that were not caused by some known medical condition.
Seizures are caused by disturbances in the electrical activity of the brain.
Epilepsy is the fourth most common neurological disorder and affects people of all ages.
Any one, any age, any where can develop epilepsy. There are 65million peop
worldwide, 2million of those people in the United States, who have epileps
There are 150,000 new cases of epilepsy in the US each year.
1 OUT OF 10 PEOPLE WILL EXPERIENCE A SEIZURE AT SOME POINT IN THEIR LIFE.
